article.headline: ETSU 63, Gardner-Webb 61
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. (AP) -- Reserve Dequan Twilley made two layups down the stretch to help East Tennessee State hold off Gardner-Webb 63-61 Friday night for the Bucs' ninth straight Atlantic Sun victory. East Tennessee (17-7, 11-1) held the Runnin' Bulldogs (7-16, 5-7) scoreless after Grayson Flittner made two free throws with 2:52 left to put Gardner-Webb ahead 61-56. Twilley made his layups in the next minute, then Eryk Thomas scored with 1:10 left to push the Bucs ahead 62-61. Mike Smith added a free throw with eight seconds left for the final score. Smith led East Tennessee with 14 points, Courtney Pigram and Andrew Reed had 12 each, Thomas scored 10 and Twilley had nine. Gardner-Webb, which hit 10-of-18 3-pointers, was led by Thomas Sanders with 16 points and Chris Gash with 11. The Runnin' Bulldogs led 59-50 on two free throws by Gash with 4:48 left until East Tennessee rallied.
